## Key Rules

### API (Go)
- Config is loaded once in `config.Load()` — never read env vars directly in handlers
- All modules are initialized in `bootstrap/bootstrap.go` in the correct order
- HTTP handlers return `{"data": ...}` on success, `{"error": "..."}` on failure
- Auth middleware reads Bearer token from `Authorization` header, puts user in context
- Use `api.UserFromContext(r.Context())` to get the authenticated user in handlers

### Frontend (Next.js)
- API client is in `src/lib/api.ts` — use `api.get()`, `api.post()` etc.
- Auth is handled by Clerk — use `useUser()` hook for client components
- All pages use the App Router (`src/app/`)

### Database
- Migrations are in `apps/api/migrations/` (SQL files)
- Run `make migrate` to apply migrations
- Use `make migrate-create` to create a new migration

### Development
- `make setup` — install deps + start infra
- `make dev` — start API + web concurrently
- `make test` — run Go tests
- `make lint` — lint Go + TypeScript

